					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">OneCrudeDude wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Here's an idea; sprite for middle weapon and magic bottles; the protagonist is a bluish color, so his palette could be used here.  I'm not sure what the scale thing is supposed to hold in the end, and the one image I seen looks like they're all similar enough in color.  Alternatively, magic is turned into a sprite based magic bar with a value mark (IE:  1/4).</div><br /><br />Well, there are a few problems with using sprites. The player changes color when you get a new armor (same as the rings in Zelda 1) and the magic bar fills up all the way to the edge of the screen. Sure it could be shortened but I think it would be nicer if it would stay the same. The &quot;scale&quot; holds the orbs you get when finishing a castle, it's basically the triforce. On the Master System all orbs are different colors but here they would all have to look the same, no biggie.<br /><br />Here's an update to Golden Axe Warrior using palette changes, there's two scanlines of black in the beginning of the status bar, and three of the palettes are changed. <br /><br /><img src="http://driar.se/pic/nes/goldenaxewarrior_statusbar.png" alt="Image" /></div>

					
